<div dir="ltr"><div><div>Sayed,<br><br></div>You might try this link (or have your sysadmin do it if you do not have admin privileges.) To me it looks like your second port is in the &quot;INIT&quot; state but has not been added by the subnet manager.<br>
<br><a href="https://software.intel.com/en-us/articles/troubleshooting-infiniband-connection-issues-using-ofed-tools">https://software.intel.com/en-us/articles/troubleshooting-infiniband-connection-issues-using-ofed-tools</a><br>
<br>You might also try try running only over port 1 with the mca parameter:<br><br></div><div>-mca btl_openib_if_include mlx4_0:1<br><br></div><div>Hope this helps.<br><br></div>Josh <br></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br>
